
Product Overview
An intelligent mastering solution designed to accelerate your workflow while delivering professional-grade results. The plugin combines smart analysis, analog-modeled processing, and flexible tonal shaping in a streamlined interface.

Intelligent Mastering Assistant
The built-in analysis engine examines your track's loudest section to generate tailored suggestions specific to your audio material. Ten Smart Presets are automatically created based on this analysis, with every adjustment level-matched to maintain consistent perceived loudness as you audition options.

Navigate presets instantly using the dedicated arrow controls, or "lock" individual modules to preserve your favorite settings while exploring alternative configurations elsewhere in the chain.

Reference Track Integration: Import your own reference material to build custom sonic profiles. Compare your work against your target and steer your master toward the desired result with precision.

Dynamics Processing
Class-A Discrete Compressor: A transformer-balanced compressor offering three operational modes—Stereo, Dual-Mono, and Mid/Side—for comprehensive control over your stereo field.

Two-Stage Architecture: Independent Optical and Discrete compression sections enable sophisticated serial compression techniques, allowing you to shape transients and sustain separately.

Output Transformer Selection: Choose from three distinct transformer characters:

Nickel: Adds airy top-end sparkle
Iron: Introduces subtle midrange character
Steel: Provides additional harmonic saturation
Equalization
Five-Band Parametric EQ: Mastering-grade equalization delivering precision, flexibility, and musical detail. Features include:

Q-Curve Flexibility: Independently switch between Constant Q and Proportional Q across all five bands for targeted boosts and cuts
Auto Listen: Isolate EQ effects to accurately position filters within the frequency spectrum
Variable High-Pass and Low-Pass Filters with dedicated controls
Low-Frequency Management:

Mono Maker: Sums content below 200 Hz to mono for focused, punchy bass response
Octave Filler: Extends and enriches low-end extension
Stereo Field Control:

Stereo Width: Expand the stereo image of your tracks
M/S Processing: Full mid/side capability for independent mono and stereo information processing
Analysis Tools: Integrated FFT spectrum analyzer with real-time visual feedback.

Analog Tone Shaping
Class-A Tube Circuitry: Transformer-balanced design with custom high-headroom transformers and variable THD for controlled saturation.

Unique Digital Fingerprint: Each license generates a model specific to your serial number, ensuring a distinct sonic character.

Baxandall EQ Section: Three-band design with Pultec-inspired low-end response.

Specialized Filters:

AIR: Enhances top-end presence and sheen
TIGHT: Cleans up low-frequency mud
Character Switches:

VINTAGE: Smooths aggressive top-end frequencies
ASPECT RATIO: Enhances stereo image width and depth
GAIN LINK: Streamlines gain staging across modules
Extended Control:

HEADROOM Knob: Adjust internal operating levels for optimal signal flow
OUTPUT TRIM: ±10 dB of analog-modeled gain adjustment
CIRCUIT BEND: Access distorted and degraded textures for creative applications
Metering: Stereo output meter displaying both RMS and peak levels with automatic internal oversampling.

Multi-Stage Saturation
MOJO Amplifiers: Three distinct amp models delivering multi-stage saturation with varying harmonic characteristics.

Colour Modules: Five specialized modules providing diverse tonal effects and texture options.

Tape Emulation
Authentic analog tape saturation with precise modeling of tape machine behavior.

Modern Enhancements (Ultimate Mode): Improved clarity, spatiality, and frequency control for contemporary production workflows.

Tape Machine Controls:

Selectable Tape Speed: 15 ips or 30 ips operation
High-Speed Recording Simulation
Drive Parameter: Extended resolution for detailed saturation control
Tone Adjustments:

Low Frequency Adjust: Compensates for head resonance and tape speed artifacts
High Frequency Adjust: Fine resolution for precise tonal shaping
Dynamic Response: Authentic tape compression behavior without unwanted artifacts—no crosstalk, pre/post echoes, or noise floor interference.

Workflow Features
Quick A/B Comparison Mode: Instantly compare processed and unprocessed signals
Scalable User Interface: Adapt the interface to your screen and workflow preferences
Artist Presets: Curated starting points from professional engineers
Mono Version Available: Dedicated mono variant for processing individual elements (kick, snare, bass, vocals, etc.)
